Sentencas: Ce-doped La0.7Sr0.3Fe0.5Cr0.5O3-delta (Ce-LSFC) perovskite anode catalysts for solid oxide fuel cells are successfully synthesized by a modified combustion method for the first time.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance and carbon deposition resistance of Ce-doped La0.7Sr0.3Fe0.5Cr0.5O3-δ anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells fed with syngas

Sentencas: The pure perovskite structure without formation of CeO2 is obtained when the content of Ce <= 10%.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance and carbon deposition resistance of Ce-doped La0.7Sr0.3Fe0.5Cr0.5O3-δ anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells fed with syngas

Sentencas: Compared with La0.7Sr0.3Fe0.5Cr0.5O3-delta anode, Ce-LSFC anode not only shows much higher catalytic activity towards the oxidation of syngas with less carbon deposition, but also displays better regeneration from coking.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance and carbon deposition resistance of Ce-doped La0.7Sr0.3Fe0.5Cr0.5O3-δ anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells fed with syngas

Sentencas: The enhanced performance is attributed to the more available oxygen vacancies in lattice and better oxygen mobility after doping with Ce.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance and carbon deposition resistance of Ce-doped La0.7Sr0.3Fe0.5Cr0.5O3-δ anode materials for solid oxide fuel cells fed with syngas
